# Fun to Give - Next.js Project Structure

This is a Next.js 13+ project using the app directory structure. The main entry point is [app/page.tsx](mdc:app/page.tsx) which serves as the homepage.

## Key Directories:
- **app/**: Main application directory (Next.js 13+ app router)
  - **components/**: Reusable UI components
    - **ui/**: Basic UI components like buttons, cards, inputs
    - **cursor/**: Custom cursor components
    - **scroll/**: Scroll-related animations
    - **loadpage/**: Loading page components
  - **pages/**: Page components (not routes, but content sections)
  - **contexts/**: React contexts for state management
  - **hooks/**: Custom React hooks
  - **lib/**: Utility functions and configurations
  - **fonts/**: Custom font definitions
  - **styles/**: Additional CSS files

## Component Guidelines:
- Use TypeScript for all components
- Follow the "use client" directive for client-side components
- Use Framer Motion for animations
- Implement RTL (right-to-left) support for Hebrew text
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling with custom color palette

## Color Palette:
- Primary: #97cabc (mint green)
- Secondary: #f2a283 (coral)
- Background: #fdf6ed (cream)
